-EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> This may have been, for them, an unquantifiable unknown for them in their balancing process.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Indeed.  And it may have been very difficult for them to understand how and why it occured, especially if, as I suspect, it was an inobvious consequence of the interaction of the game geometry with client/server lag.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It's more the principle of letting potential balance factors be out of your control.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That is possible too.  I do not think <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> really understood the consequences, but fear that it was trivially and reliably replicated, which <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>would</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> be unbalancing if true.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I dont think we should focus on &quot;restoring&quot; double bolts...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->As I said, I thought now was the appropriate time to ask, at least once, since the change is so recent.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;this poster&quot; happens to be a mod on the forum...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->The fact that I am a moderator has almost no bearing on this discussion, except in so far as I should be careful not to be seen as bullying anyone.  My opinion bears no special weight by virtue of being a moderator, nor would I ever use my administrative powers to stifle debate, whether by moving a thread from GENERAL, locking a thread I did not like or felt should no longer be discussed, or editing posts that I thought insulted or denigrated me.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If there was somehow, someway, to make the &quot;random double bolt&quot; an AA skill so that is was supposed to work that way, perhaps. . .<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->A caster archetype or magician class skill excludes the majority of working mages.  For example, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Neutral Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> solves a lot more problems than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> ever could.  Even though I am an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ArchMage</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with 50 AA points, I am dubious about solutions that involve only AA skills.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'm against adding back in content that was a bug in the first place...However, I can't see the rational of asking to give us a bug that wasn't supposed to happen.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I may have some history mistaken here, as I was not directly involved at the time, but as I recall a similar issue arose over the use of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Feign Death</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and pulling.  As described in a previous post, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Feign Death</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> was intended to be nothing more than a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Get out of Jail FREE&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> card, when skilled pullers discovered ways to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;exploit&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> it for splitting pulls.  This was an unintended consequence of the game mechanics and was definitely considered to be an exploit initially.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Feign Death</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> either was or was about to be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;fixed&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;nerfed&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> when the monk community rose up in arms and insisted that it remain as it was before.  As we all well know, they were successful.  While I do not suggest that this issue is of nearly that importance, it means that the argument <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;It was a bug, they fixed it, end of story&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is not necessarily a compelling one.  So was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Feign Death</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pulling.<br>
<br>
For students of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> zen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I offer this simple <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> koan</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to meditate upon: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;What is the difference between a bug and a feature?&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Putting double bolts back in is similar in effect to giving us innate crits - and that very minor piece of eye candy is (IMO) wizard territory.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Perhaps.  And it is not my intention to intrude on wizard territory.  However, even the patch message acknowledges that double bolts were the province of mages.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> We already have a way to get increased damage on occasion out of ALL of our nukes - SCF.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->In practice, only reasonable for ArchMages, who hardly represent the majority of players.  In any case, double bolts required the application of knowledge, terrain, a keen eye and judgment, none of which are required for a straight percentage damage increase.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> But the idea in and of itself lead to a number of interesting possibilities that, at the very least, could be discussed rationally instead of being dismissed out of hand.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Discussion is always good, and can give rise to new and better ideas not intended by the original author.<br>
<br>
There are larger issues wrapped up in this, that have real consequences for mages.  What is a bug?  What is an exploit?  What is a fair application of game mechanics to a player's advantage, and how do we distinguish among the three?  Today it is double bolts, tomorrow it may be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Reclaim Energy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  And are we to have an open discussion of our strengths and weakness, or shall we parade our weaknesses in the hopes that they will be fixed while obsuring our best tactics in the hope of preserving them?<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> more so for going out on a limb and posting his opinion.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Ironically, it is not even my opinion I am expressing here, but the opinion of others that I have once again collected, summarized, and refined.  This is not the first time I have done this: previously I posted a detailed petition in favor of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=90.topic">Reduce Pet Penalties</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> even my point of view was better represented by <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=82.topic">Increased Pet Strength</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
I read this board carefully, with an open mind, to learn from those whose experience and opinions differ from my own.  It is in that spirit, and in the spirit of open discussion, then I submitted this thread in the first place.<br>
